  Somewhere in the silky smooth slopes of Symphagos lives a masked mammal named Rack Bandit, and one day I happened upon this curious creature devouring vile vibrations.  Despite its disheveled demeanor, this devious detritivore is endowed with dazzling dexterity, focusing on fixed frequencies that correspond to critical bands of human hearing: A creative "critter call band EQ" with an analog twist.
  
  Let Rack Bandit devour your band racket!
  
  Place this precocious peak pocket on your tracks, using crosstalk (fluff) to smooth out sharp curves, and transformer (underfur) for a deep warm analog effect. Turn up the chitter with the drive knob for extra bite, and parallel process with the mix knob (dousing).  For additional analog attributes, toggling "rocky" mode will activate asymmetric saturation and proportional Q; a true retro revival.
  
